##########Run this in windows powershell Terminal#####################
This is all run after installing WSL and Ubuntu to run the script in a Linux environment.
Initial installation and setup of genomic tools
- sudo apt-get install seaview
- sudo apt-get install muscle
-----------Install PLINK---------------------- 
- Linux file from this link https://www.cog-genomics.org/plink/2.0/
- in WSL set directory cd/mnt/c/Users/dhyay/OneDrive/Desktop/Sars_cov_analysis
- Unzip file - unzip plink2_linux_avx2_20250604.zip
- Execute the file - chmod +x plink2
- Move to path - sudo mv plink2 /usr/local/bin/
- test - plink2 --help (Plink help manual should appear)
------------Install Pangolin-----------------
- conda create -n pangolin -c bioconda -c conda-forge pangolin
- conda activate pangolin
- conda install -c bioconda seqkit (to use to help split the file into batches)
- seqkit split -s 200 1643_genomes.fasta_c.txt (split the data into 200 batches)
--------------Install IQTREE--------------------
- wget https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
- bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
- source ~/miniconda3/etc/profile.d/conda.sh
	- conda --version
- echo 'source ~/miniconda3/etc/profile.d/conda.sh' >> ~/.bashrc
- conda install -c bioconda iqtree
--------------Install JBROWSE-------------------
- sudo apt-get install nodejs npm
- mkdir ~/.npm-global
- npm config set prefix '~/.npm-global'
- export PATH=~/.npm-global/bin:$PATH
- source ~/.bashrc
- npm install -g @jbrowse/cli
--------------Install Jvarkit--------------------
- sudo apt-get update
#switch to an earlier version due to compatibility issues
- sudo apt-get install openjdk-8-jdk
- java -version  # Confirm Java 8 is installed
# Download the source code archive for jvarkit v20200206
- wget https://github.com/lindenb/jvarkit/archive/refs/tags/v20200206.zip
# Unzip the archive
- unzip v20200206.zip
# Change to the jvarkit directory
- cd jvarkit-20200206
# Build the msa2vcf tool using Gradle
- ./gradlew msa2vcf
# After a successful build, confirm the JAR file exists
- ls dist/msa2vcf.jar
